# autoresearch-{{SLUG}}

Self-improving loop for the `{{SKILL_NAME}}` skill, modeled on [karpathy/autoresearch](https://github.com/karpathy/autoresearch).

## Files

| File | Role | Mutable? |
|---|---|---|
| `program.md` | Loop driver instructions | No |
| `Skill.md` | The skill prompt being iterated on (copy of live) | **Yes — edited by the loop** |
| `eval.mjs` | Programmatic checks | No |
| `judge-prompt.md` | LLM judge rubric | No |
| `inputs/pool.tsv` | Rotating inputs | No |
| `results.tsv` | Per-cycle log | Appended; gitignored |
| `scratch/` | Generated samples per cycle | Gitignored |

## Run it

```
cd {{PROJECT_DIR}}
claude
```

Then: `Read program.md and run the autoresearch loop.`

The loop stops after 30 cycles or when it hits 3 consecutive perfect cycles on different inputs.

## Promote the result

```
diff {{LIVE_SKILL_PATH}} ./Skill.md
```

If you like the diff, copy over manually. The loop never touches the live skill.

